<l>neṭṭeḻut timparum toṭarmoḻi yīṟṟuṅ</l>
<l>kuṟṟiya lukaram vallā ṟūrntē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The overshort <foreign xml:lang="ta">u</foreign> will appear following an occlusive</l>
<l>which occurs after long vowel, and in the final</l>
          <l>position of a <foreign xml:lang="ta">toṭarmoḻi</foreign>.<note place="foot">In this c., <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">toṭarmoḻi</foreign> = polysyllabic (i.e. more than disyllabic) word,
            e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">va-ra-ku</foreign> ' millet '. and disyllabic word of the pattern - u (e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">teṅku</foreign> ' coconut tree ').</note></l>
          </l>
      </lg>
    </div>
